Short:    TrueTypeFont Viewer
Author:   Diego Casorran
Uploader: <dcr8520@amiga.org>
Version:  0.1
Type:     util/cdity
Requires: 68020+ & ttengine.library


This tool let you know, in a workbench window, what typedef are available
at the desired font. It must be run from cli, getting as argument, the full
path to the TTFont.

I wrote this little tool to be able to load a ttfont from dopus4 quickly,
and then check his style and the following characters:

ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ
abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz
0123456789[\]!"#$%&'()*+×¿
